Subject: Re: Linux is already heavily used in business !!!
Date: Mon, 30 Aug 1993 06:03:19 GMT

In article <CCGEFF.3J1@serveme.chi.il.us> greg@serveme.chi.il.us (Gregory Gulik) writes:
>In article <CCCC2F.Hx@bigcomm.gun.de> ado@bigcomm.gun.de (Christoph Adomeit) writes:
>>
>>Maybe one day we could give Big Bill a Linux-copy so that he can afford an os:-)
>
>Better not.  He might like it and have his lawyers figure out how
>he could sell it to make himself a few more billion $$$..

The free software foundation has nothing against people making 
money off software.  However, the party line is that people are 
paying for support, development, and other value added services
rather than the software itself that is free.

So, someone making a few more billion off Linux in itself
wouldn't be a bad thing, and it would be a definite improvement
in quality compared to many of the current Microsoft offerings.

The part about William taking a Liking to Linux I object to is that
his lawyers would find a way to break the GPL, and his programmers would
find a way to break Linux so they could sell the next revision as a bug
fix.
