From: entropy@world.std.com (Lawrence Foard)
Subject: Re: Stacker-like Compression?
Date: Mon, 30 Aug 1993 06:42:19 GMT

I've got all of the code needed for a generic compressed block device accept
for code that takes a fixed size block and compresses it. If any
one wants to send me some good block compression code I'll put it
into this and post it.

Of course it wouldn't be wise to trust important files to it until
its been tested quite a bit. But it would be nice for infrequently
used system files which can be easily replaced if it blows up.
